---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icon.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About">
	<div class="stack gap-20">
		<main class="wrapper" style="grid-template-columns: 0 !important;">
			<Hero>
				
			</Hero>

			<style>
				p {
					font-weight: 600 !important;
				}
				.dashed {
					position: relative;
					padding-bottom: 25px;
					margin-top: 30px;
					font-size: 45px;
				}

				.dashed::after {
					content: "";
					position: absolute;
					display: block;
					width: 50px;
					height: 3px;
					background: var(--accent-dark);
					bottom: 16px;
					left: 0;
				}

				
				.mt0 {
					padding-bottom: 15px;
				}

				.pres {
					box-shadow: none !important;
					height: 54px;
					margin-top: 1rem !important;
				}

				.icon-container {
					margin-bottom: 20px;
					display: flex;
					gap: 5px;
				}

				.icon-container div {
					display: flex;
					flex-direction: column;
				}

				.icon-container div img {
					height: 70px;
					width: 70px;
					margin: auto;
				}

				.icon-container div p {
					text-align: center;
					font-size: 15px;
					font-weight: 100;
					color: var(--gray-200);
				}

				a {
					text-decoration: none;
				}

				@media(max-width: 800px) {
					#passions {
						display: block;
					}

					#passions .passion {
						width: calc(100% - 50px)
					}
				}

				.about {
					display: flex;
					flex-direction: column;
					gap: 3.5rem;
				}

				img {
					margin-top: 1.5rem;
					border-radius: 1.5rem;
					box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
				}

				section {
					display: flex;
					flex-direction: column;
					gap: 0.5rem;
					color: var(--gray-200);
				}

				.section-title {
					grid-column-start: 1;
					font-size: var(--text-xl);
					color: var(--gray-0);
				}

				.content {
					grid-column: 2 / 4;
				}

				.content :global(a) {
					text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
					text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
					transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
				}

				.content :global(a:hover),
				.content :global(a:focus) {
					text-decoration-color: currentColor;
				}

				@media (min-width: 50em) {
					.about {
						display: grid;
						grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
					}

					.about > :global(:first-child) {
						grid-column-start: 2;
					}

					section {
						display: contents;
						font-size: var(--text-lg);
					}
				}

				b {
					font-weight: 600;
				}

				h4 {
					font-weight: 600;
					
					margin-top: 35px;
					margin-bottom: 10px;
  					font-size: 26px;
				}

				.bolder {
					background: var(--accent-dark);
					background-clip: border-box;
					background-clip: border-box;
					-webkit-background-clip: text;
					-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;

					font-weight: 900;
				}

				.card {
					border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255, 0.25);
				background-color: rgba(30, 31, 48, 0.30);
				box-shadow: 0 0 10px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25);
				padding: 10px 25px;
				font-weight: 700;
				border-radius: 20px;
				}
			</style>

			<section>
				<div class="content">
					<h2 class="dashed">About</h2>


					<h4 class="bolder"><a href="#backend">Backend</a></h4>
					<div>
						I am a web developer with a strong background in web backend development, specializing in <b>Vanilla-PHP</b> and the <b>Laravel</b> Framework with 
						<b>Livewire</b>. Consequently, I am well-versed in the PHP ecosystem and have extensive experience with <b>Composer</b>. Additionally, I have proficient knowledge of <b>SQL and NoSQL</b>, which allows me to build robust backends.
					</div>

					<h4 class="bolder"><a href="#frontend">Frontend</a></h4>
					<div>
						I also have extensive experience in front-end development, adeptly working with CSS frameworks such as 
						<b>Bootstrap</b> and <b>Tailwind</b>. 
						I have worked with a variety of JavaScript packages including <b>Swiper.js, ChartJS, HTMX, and Pusher</b>, among others. <br>
						I'm currenly learning <b>React</b>. Therefore, I also have good knowledges of <b>NPM</b> and of the <b>Vite.Js</b> bundler.
					</div>

					<h4 class="bolder"><a href="#devops">DevOps</a></h4>
					<div>
						Beyond that, I'm also a huge fan of SysAdmin and DevOps. Currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Networking, 
						I work with <b>GNU/Linux</b> on a daily basis. Therefore, I am very familiar with different package managers, 
						tools (<b>Docker, docker-compose, git</b>), application layer services (<b>HTTP, (S)FTP, SSH, SMB ...</b>), and command line interfaces (<b>bash, zsh ..</b>). 
					</div>
					
				</div>  

				
